# Outputs of tools/vendor-rust.R. The vendored engine snapshot and offline
# cargo tarball ARE committed so the repo is self-contained and builds from a
# clean clone (required by R-universe, which builds from the repo, not from a
# pre-vendored tarball). Re-run tools/vendor-rust.R and re-commit these on
# every PINNED_REV bump. Local unpack dirs stay ignored.
src/vendor/
src/.cargo/

# Rendered pkgdown/albersdown site and stray local package extractions.
# Both are .Rbuildignore'd already; keep them out of git too. The site is
# published from CI, not committed; /vendor/ is a local unpack, not source.
/docs/
/vendor/
# scratch (also in .Rbuildignore as ^tmp$)
tmp/
relib/

# testthat auto-generated failure dump — regenerated on failing runs, not source
tests/testthat/testthat-problems.rds
release-gate-report.txt
